tips: Track every single transaction in a separate spreadsheet to get a clear picture of where your money is going.
Identify areas where you can cut back on unnecessary expenses, such as subscription services or dining out too frequently.
Consider implementing the 50/30/20 rule: allocate 50% of your income towards necessary expenses, 30% towards discretionary spending, and 20% towards saving and debt repayment.
advice.quick_win: Implement a 'stop doing' list to eliminate one unnecessary expense or subscription service each month.
advice.positive: You're taking the first step towards gaining control over your finances! Keep up the good work and remember that small changes add up over time.
